content.problemStatement:
A binary tree is a tree data structure in which each node has at most two children, referred to as the left child and the right child. This characteristic distinguishes binary trees from other tree structures that allow more than two children per node.

Now there are multiple types of binary trees, let's look into them one at a time.      


